The Story Begins: Why Your Upload Button Is Just The Beginning

ūüĎ¶ Nephew: Uncle! I finally built my RAG system. User uploads a PDF, system finds answers. Simple, right?

ūüĎ®‚Äćūü¶≥ Uncle: (smiles knowingly) You uploaded a PDF and got an answer?

ūüĎ¶ Nephew: Yes! It works!

ūüĎ®‚Äćūü¶≥ Uncle: Did you get the right answer?

ūüĎ¶ Nephew: Well... sometimes. Why?

ūüĎ®‚Äćūü¶≥ Uncle: Because between "user uploads PDF" and "system creates embeddings", there are 15 critical steps. Skip even one, and your system fails silently. You get wrong answers and don't know why.

ūüĎ¶ Nephew: 15 steps? I just embedded the text!

ūüĎ®‚Äćūü¶≥ Uncle: Exactly. That's the problem. Come, let me show you what production engineers actually do.

The 15 Steps of Phase 1: Document Ingestion

ūüĎ®‚Äćūü¶≥ Uncle: Think of it like cooking biryani. You don't just dump rice and meat, right?

ūüĎ¶ Nephew: No, you prepare everything first!

ūüĎ®‚Äćūü¶≥ Uncle: Exactly. Before you cook, you:

‚ÄĘ Wash rice

‚ÄĘ Soak rice

‚ÄĘ Prepare meat

‚ÄĘ Marinate meat

‚ÄĘ Chop onions

‚ÄĘ ... and many more steps

Only THEN you cook.

The same with documents. Before embeddings, you must:

1. Document Upload (user action)
2. File Hashing (did we see this before?)
3. PDF Parsing (extract text)
4. Text Extraction (convert PDF ‚Üí text)
5. Text Cleaning (remove junk)
6. Metadata Extraction (add context)
7. Chunking (split smartly)
8. Chunk Boundaries (don't break meaning)
9. Chunk Size (1000 tokens, not 100)
10. Overlap (context continuity)
11. Chunk Hashing (detect changes)
12. Deduplication (prevent duplicates)
13. Versioning (handle updates)
14. Incremental Ingestion (avoid re-embedding)
15. Cost Optimization (save money)
ONLY THEN:
‚Üď
Embeddings
‚Üď
Vector DB

